Subject:    <a href="?t=95837890900028&r=1&w=2">Root Nameserver Question</a>
From:       <a href="?a=95837786200032&r=1&w=2">Marty Hoag &lt;NU021172 () VM1 ! NoDak ! EDU&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198906">1989-06-01 10:40:21</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626924&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626924&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

   We recently had some problems resolving a domain added to the dns last
week, KESTREL.EDU.  Upon investigation I found that the root nameservers
(as listed in the file at sri-nic and in the ns records for EDU) were
not all at the same levels.  I noticed this over last weekend and sent
a note to the "NS" listed contacts yesterday but got no response.

   Today they are all at serial 890530 for EDU EXCEPT the following:

           C.NYSER.NET   192.33.4.12      is at  890522
           TERP.UMD.EDU  10.1.0.17        is at  890519
                         128.8.10.90

   Depending upon connectivity to the other root nameservers this can
mean that answers will vary depending on which root is used as authoritative.

   Is this a common occurence or are those nameservers just broken at the
moment?

   Are there any established standards for refresh currency for the root
nameservers?

   Any information would be appreciated.  I am not on the namedroppers list
at this time so please include me in any reply.  Thank you!

